{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Off-rolling of pupils should be done through Ofsted or other independent body ",
        "additional_details": "The off-rolling is an issue when the institution in case does it for it's own benefit and not for the child's best interest. To prevent any injustice to be done to a child or parent a designated governing body should hold the decision, not the institution's management.\r\n\r\nTo prevent the institution verbally convincing a parent to move their child, a form that questions that should be required to be completed by the parent when relocating schools/nurseries and analysed by the same governing body.",
        "background": "The Government should designate an independent body, such as Ofsted to investigate the reasons of any nursery/school asking for a child's relocation. This shouldn't be done without this body's approval and must include cases where parents are working in the same institution as their child studies.",
